<BLOCK1><TI>Notice of APPLICATION (For judicial review)</TI>
<P>This is an application for judicial review in respect of</P>
<P>Two letters received from the Canada Revenue Agency International tax services office:</P>
<BLOCK2><TI><UNDER>1<SUP>st</SUP> letter on August 23, 2012</UNDER></TI>
<P>This letter declined my appeal for relief from the application of penalty for late filing of my 2010 nonresident income tax return.</P>
<P>The letter gave me the option to appeal the decision based on section 18.1, which I did (court file no. T-116-13).</P>
<P>This application/proceedings had reached the stage where I had submitted written cross examination to the respondent.</P>
<P>However the respondents counsel at the time Mr Ricky Tang called me to say that I had produced some valid arguments in my cross examination and he verily believes that my appeal should be granted. So he does not see any benefit in taking this matter any further and will send the file back to Revenue Canada to make the necessary adjustments.</P>
<P>He did mention that in order to do this, I would have to sign a notice of discontinuance, which I did on or around May 6<SUP>th</SUP> 2013.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><UNDER>2<SUP>nd</SUP> letter on July 23, 2013</UNDER></TI>
<P>This letter once again declined my appeal for relief from the application of penalty for late filing of my 2010 nonresident income tax return.</P>
<P>The letter has once again given me the option to appeal the decision based on section 18.1, which means I will now have to start the entire process all over.</P>
<P>The applicant makes application for:</P>
<P>I am asking that the Honorable Judge of the Federal Court of Canada grant me relief from the application of penalty for late filing of my 2010 nonresident income tax return.</P>
<P>The grounds for the application are:
<P1>1. Failed to observe a principle of procedural fairness.</P1>
<P1>2. Did not adequately consider extraordinary circumstances.</P1></P>
<P>This application will be supported by the following material: (List the supporting affidavits, including documentary exhibits, and the portions of transcripts to be used.)
<P1>1. Supporting affidavit of Gregory Sailsman including documentary exhibits.</P1></P>
<P>(Date) August 21, 2013</P>
<P>&ellip35; (Signature of solicitor or applicant)</P>
<P>(Gregory Sailsman: XXXXXXXXXX Tele# XXXXXXXXXX, Fax# XXXXXXXXXX)</P></BLOCK2></BLOCK1>
